Ad Text:
About Us

The National Basketball League (NBL) is a world-renowned basketball organisation, home to some of the globe’s best players. As a leader in sports entertainment, we operate an innovative media platform and are dedicated to achieving new heights of success and growth. Our vision is to be the most entertaining sports experience for fans, through bold innovation and partnerships, and to become the fastest growing league globally.

Our Values 

Always Think Big: Be courageous, be open to new ideas, learn and grow — no limits.
Be Accountable: Own it! Ask for help. The scoreboard matters.
Integrity is Key: Act ethically, act honestly, keep our word.
Show Respect: Show care, listen and seek to understand, value opinions.
We are Fans Too: Have fun, always consider the fan, share the love of the game.
One Team: Communicate, trust each other, celebrate the wins, build relationships.
About This Opportunity

As a Data Engineer you'll be working closely with our analytics, digital, and commercial teams, you’ll ensure data flows seamlessly across systems and empower the League to make smarter, faster, and more impactful decisions on and off the court.

What You’ll Do Build & Optimise Data Infrastructure

Design and manage scalable, secure data pipelines across multiple platforms (ticketing, broadcast, digital, player and game data)
Maintain and enhance the League’s central data warehouse as a single source of truth
Integrate complex datasets to enable real-time insights and long-term strategic analysis
Ensure Data Quality & Governance

Implement rigorous quality and validation frameworks to ensure clean, accurate, and compliant data
Support data privacy and governance requirements in alignment with industry best practices
Monitor and resolve data issues across systems and partners
Collaborate & Drive Insights

Partner with internal stakeholders to deliver data solutions aligned with business priorities
Work closely with analysts and data scientists to structure and prepare datasets for advanced modelling
Collaborate with vendors, clubs, and partners to improve interoperability and data flow across the NBL ecosystem
Innovate & Improve Continuously

Drive automation and innovation in data collection and analytics
Explore emerging technologies to enhance fan engagement, commercial growth, and on-court analytics
Stay ahead of industry trends in sports data and digital transformation
What We’re Looking For

Essential Skills & Experience

Strong SQL and database management skills (relational and non-relational)
Proven experience with data warehousing, ETL, and data modelling
Familiarity with big data or streaming technologies (e.g., Spark, Kafka) and APIs
Understanding of data governance, privacy, and compliance
Ability to translate complex data concepts for non-technical audiences.
Strong problem-solving and communication skills with a collaborative mindset
Commercially aware, detail-oriented, and passionate about sport and technology
Desirable

Experience in sports, entertainment, or media industries
Tertiary qualifications in Computer Science, Data Engineering, or related fields
Exposure to cloud-based data solutions and analytics tools
Why Join the NBL?

Impact: Drive decisions that shape the future of basketball in Australia.
Innovation: Work with modern tools, platforms, and data technologies.
Culture: Join a passionate, high-performing team that lives and breathes the game.
Growth: Be part of NBL’s digital transformation and rapid expansion.
Variety: Work across diverse data sources – from live game analytics to fan experience platforms.
Ready to Join the Team? 

If you’re passionate about data, innovation, and sport, this is your chance to make an impact at the heart of Australia’s premier basketball league.

Apply now and help us turn data into the next big play

The National Basketball League is dedicated to championing diversity and inclusion. We wholeheartedly embrace individual differences and warmly welcome all qualified applicants to apply, including First Nations peoples.

Work with cutting edge AI technology, making the world a safer and more secure place. DroneShield (ASX:DRO) offers an opportunity to solve some of world's most challenging technical problems in the rapidly growing counterdrone sector. Our customers are militaries, government agencies, airports, critical infrastructure, law enforcement and many others.




With one of the largest listed defence company market capitalisations in Australia, part of the ASX200 index, and having raised approximately $250m in 2024 alone, DroneShield is undergoing hypergrowth stage, fuelled by rapidly increasing use of drones for nefarious applications, from battlefield, to terrorism, to contraband delivery and commercial espionage.




This role is in the DroneShield Sydney headquarters in Sydney CBD. There are approximately 380 staff based in the 4,000sqm facility today, scheduled to grow to approximately 500 staff by end of 2026. Overseas on the ground presence includes Virginia (USA), Netherlands, Denmark, Mexico and Dubai, as well as distributors in over 70 countries globally.







About the role

DroneShield is seeking a Software Engineer with relevant experience to join the team in Sydney, NSW.

The primary focus of the role is to develop and maintain DroneShield's Linux based deployed sensors. Working closely with ML/AI, Data Science, Embedded, RF and infrastructure teams to innovate and enhance DroneShield's world leading RF detection technology.

This is an exceptional opportunity for a results-driven individual in a rapidly expanding market.




Responsibilities, Duties and Expectations

Design and implement new software features for Linux-based systems
Ensure software is designed for performance and reliability on resource constrained targets
Collaborate with multi-disciplinary teams, including algorithms and FPGA, to deliver on user and business requirements
Work with the broader engineering team to ensure reliable and robust end to end system operation
Write and maintain internal documentation for implemented features

Qualifications, Experience and Skills

BS degree in Computer Science, Information Technology or similar technical field of study or equivalent practical experience
Experience using modern C++ and/or Python to develop complex applications
Familiarity with developing under Linux (embedded Linux would be advantageous)
Experience with multi-process architectures (including IPC mechanisms)
Proficiency working with systems composed of multiple programming languages
Experience designing and architecting software solutions
Experience with development tools including Git, Jira, Confluence, GitLab CI/CD, Docker

The following would also be highly desirable:

Experience with concurrent computing and code optimization
DevOps experience, including CI/CD, automated testing, and system monitoring
Strong proficiency with Docker
Experience with ML, RF, FPGA, and DSP technologies




Note for recruitment agencies: We do not accept unsolicited candidates from external recruiters unless specifically instructed.

About Us 

At Sportsbet, we’re all about bringing excitement to life for our 2.4 million customers. As part of the global Flutter Group, we’re a tight-knit team of 1,300 in Melbourne, Sydney, and Darwin, passionate about challenging the status quo. We’re proud to be recognized as one of LinkedIn’s Top 25 Companies and one of the Top 10 Workplaces for Women. 

We’re an inclusive employer who celebrates diversity and is committed to helping you thrive. Whether you’re looking for flexibility, career growth, or a supportive environment, we’re here to help you succeed. 

Committed To Responsible Gambling 

Our commitment to responsible gambling is genuine and demonstrated through the wide range of responsible gambling initiatives and tools. We’re proud to be the leaders in responsible gambling in our industry, not just locally, but globally. 

The Opportunity

At Sportsbet, we’re reimagining what’s possible with data, machine learning and AI. We’re a fast-moving, customer-obsessed business — and we’re looking for an Operational Excellence Manager to help us scale our ML capabilities, processes, practices, and governance to ensure that data science models continuously deliver measurable Customer and Business value. This is a fixed term contract role.

You’ll play a pivotal role in uplifting our end-to-end machine learning ecosystem — from model design and governance to deployment and continuous improvement. Working alongside data scientists, ML engineers and business stakeholders, you’ll help industrialise how we build, deliver, and manage models that power millions of customer experiences.

This isn’t a “keep the lights on” role — it’s about shaping the frameworks, automations and governance that let AI and ML thrive safely and efficiently at scale.

What You’ll Do

Design and implement frameworks for ML governance, lifecycle management, and operational best practice.
Work closely with Heads of Data Science teams to ensure implementation of ML best practices.
Partner with Risk, Compliance and Privacy to embed ethical AI principles and standards.
Identify inefficiencies in ML workflows and introduce automation, documentation, and streamlined processes.
Champion change management and continuous improvement across data science teams — helping others adopt and scale best practice.
Stay ahead of emerging MLOps and AI Ops trends to keep Sportsbet at the cutting edge.

What You’ll Bring

3+ years’ experience in project management, business analysis, or process improvement — ideally within data or analytics teams.
Strong understanding of ML concepts, lifecycle management, and governance.
Experience driving change and embedding frameworks across technical and non-technical stakeholders.
Excellent communication and facilitation skills.
The ability to influence key stakeholders to adopt best practices
A mindset for continuous improvement and a drive to make things simpler, faster, and better.

Why You’ll Love Working Here

Along with a competitive salary and generous performance-based bonus, here’s some of our other benefits:

25 days annual leave (plus flexible working options)
Access to outstanding career development programs, including expert-led internal training and external learning opportunities
Onsite concierge services, free meals, social events and access to the Sportsbet Salon
Generous parental leave and return-to-work benefits
Hack Days: Participate in our hack days, where creativity and collaboration lead to exciting new ideas and projects.


What’s the Green Tick Feeling?

Well, it’s different for everyone, yet unites us all. It’s the feeling you get when you succeed, no matter what success looks like to you. It could be developing your career, it could be working on an industry leading project, or it could be making it to school pick up in time. It's all the little and big things that make you feel like you’re thriving when working at Sportsbet. 

We’re an inclusive employer who welcomes you for who you are, as you are – so, if you require adjustments to the recruitment process, please let us know in your application. We also know flex means different things to different people, so let us know how we can support you to be your best. 

We review applications quickly, so apply soon! Check out our Life@Sportsbet Instagram, LinkedIn, and careers website for more about our inclusive culture.

Ready for your Green Tick Feeling? Apply now.

Salary: Our people build skills for the future
Ad Text:
Job Description

With an exciting mandate to do things differently, KPMG Futures is a specialist team set up specifically to focus on the future – including future sectors, future technologies, future services, future business models and more.  KPMG Futures pursues opportunities in areas such as quantum computing, Web 3.0, next-gen AI and start-up venture partnering.  Our main objective is to bring to life game-changing technologies and business models to accelerate a better future for our clients and KPMG.

Your Opportunity

Forming part of the AI Labs team this role will play a key role in bringing to life next-generation AI through the development of prototypes and proof of concepts (POCs) to identify potential new business opportunities for the firm and our clients.  The role will also provide input into AI-related strategy at a firmwide level and support research into responsible AI as appropriate. Your responsibilities will include:

Build prototypes & POCs in next-gen AI

Assist in driving the execution of a plan to explore, identify and test hypotheses using next gen AI to help create new businesses.

Based on the hypotheses and use case, contribute to appropriate tech stack decisions for development.

Develop on a cloud platform, like Microsoft Azure, or work with tech startups to support the execution of these hypotheses through development of prototypes and POCs. You will work across the entire AI lifecycle from data modelling, data set and database creation to model deployment leveraging your knowledge of cloud, databases, and APIs.

Capture learnings, iterate, and improve experimentation processes.

Develop a roadmap for the application of next-gen AI

Enthusiastically familiarise yourself with future tech, new tech tools and domain expertise to understand emerging AI capability.  Be curious about how the tech works algorithmically and what would be required for implementation.

Assist in identifying where and how future tech and new tech tools can create new opportunities for the firm and our clients. 

Experiment with and integrate new tech tools in prototypes and POCs to assess their value and limitations.  This includes both high and low code tech tools.

With these insights, contribute to research into next gen AI that will inform thought leadership.

Work with stakeholders within the firm and client(s)

Keep stakeholders up to date with progress and challenges, ensuring they understand the risks as well as the opportunities.

Work with stakeholders to understand the business context around the prototype and POC you develop and clearly articulate their required support for successful completion.

Assist in demo sessions to get stakeholder feedback and validate development direction.

Build credibility in Future Tech

Assist engagement with tech and research industry to build knowledge, relationships and establish the firm as a Future Tech leader.

Assist engagement with partners and alliances to form relationships that support development, enhance the firms positioning and helps to inform new business opportunity ideas.

How Are You Extraordinary?

You are a strategic critical thinker, and love using your technical skills to solve complex problems and build prototype and POC solutions in a multi-disciplinary team.

You have a can-do attitude and are always seeking creative solutions to problems with the help of the right technical tools and a supportive team.

You are passionate about the importance of fantastic communication to share ideas, inspire, and create change. You are able to digest, distil, and communicate complex concepts in both written and verbal form.

Your Experience:

At KPMG, we believe diversity of thought, background and unique experience strengthens relationships and delivers meaningful benefits to our people, our clients and communities. To be considered for this opportunity, your qualifications, skills & experience may include: 

Prior experience working within next-gen AI as a Machine Learning Engineer, Data Engineer, or Software Developer.

Experience designing, creating and orchestrating end-to-end data pipelines on a cloud platform, preferably Microsoft Azure, including:

Ingestion of structured & unstructured data sources,

Feature engineering for ML development,

Machine learning model training,

Model deployment. 

Demonstrated proficiency in Python, Java and C++, coupled with the ability to leverage SDKs and APIs to bring the best of tech all together.

Comfortable working with various development environments such as cloud platforms (Microsoft Azure) or third parties (tech start-ups) to choose and use the appropriate services to create end-to-end data pipelines.

You are a collaborative developer who leverages code base (DevOps) to use version control (git) and document their work (wiki, confluence) on the go to enable the rest of their team.

Familiarity with front end development frameworks (e.g. React.JS) will be looked upon favourably.

Ability to develop prototypes, pilots, and proof of concepts (POC).

Qualifications

Tertiary qualification (bachelor’s degree) in computer science, software development or similar.

Additional qualifications related to artificial intelligence, machine learning and/or data engineering will be considered favourably.

Relevant Microsoft Azure (or other cloud platform) certifications considered favourably.

Additional Information

KPMG is a professional services firm with global outreach and deep sector experience. We work with clients across an array of industries to solve complex challenges, steer change and enable growth. 

Our people are what make KPMG the thriving workplace that it is and what sets us apart is that we know great minds think differently. Collaborate with a team of passionate, highly skilled professionals who’ve got your back. You’ll build relationships with unique and diverse colleagues who will provide you with the support you need to be your best and produce meaningful and impactful work in an inclusive, equitable culture.

At KPMG, you’ll take control over how you work. We’re embracing a new way of working in many ways, from offering flexible hours and locations to generous paid parental leave and career breaks. Our people enjoy a variety of exciting perks, including retail discounts, health and wellbeing initiatives, learning and growth opportunities, salary packaging options and more.

Diverse candidates have diverse needs. During your recruitment journey, information will be provided about adjustment requests. If you require additional support before submitting your application, please contact the Talent Attraction Support Team.

At KPMG every career is different, and we look forward to seeing how you grow with us.

Job Title: Senior Digital Signal Processing Communications Engineer (AU)
Ad Text:
Work with cutting edge technology, making the world a safer and more secure place. DroneShield (ASX:DRO) offers an opportunity to solve some of world's most challenging technical problems in the Electronic Warfare, Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning, RF sensing, Sensor Fusion and distributed systems. Working with high profile customers across militaries, government agencies, airports, critical infrastructure, law enforcement and many others.

With one of the largest listed defence company market capitalisations in Australia and having raised approximately $250m in 2024 alone, DroneShield is undergoing hypergrowth stage, fuelled by rapidly increasing use of drones for nefarious applications, from battlefield, to terrorism, to contraband delivery and commercial espionage.

This role will be based within a new DroneShield facility based in the Adelaide CBD. Droneshield has approximately 390 staff based within its Sydney headquarters and is scheduled to grow to 500 staff in Australia by end of 2026. Overseas on the ground presence includes Virginia (USA), Denmark, Germany and Dubai, as well as distributors in over 70 countries globally.




About the role

DroneShield is seeking a Senior DSP Communications Engineer with relevant experience to join the team in Adelaide, South Australia. The position will report to the principal Architect within the Sensors and Effectors Team.




The Sensors and Effectors team at Droneshield is focused on providing fully operational and qualified modular devices to enable new product development of high-end RF based sensors and effectors. These modules are re-used across various product configurations including man-portable, vehicle mounted and fixed site. Key technical challenges for the electronics aspect of these modules include the design of complex wide-band RF circuitry, high speed digital interface and high-power radio frequency output. DroneShield designs and builds the full signal chain from signal generation to antenna.




The primary focus of the role is to research and develop DroneShield's next generation of Capabilities, working closely with ML/AI, Data Science, RF and infrastructure teams to innovate and enhance DroneShield's world leading Anti-Drone technology.




Responsibilities, Duties and Expectations

Analyse real-world wireless signals to identify modulation schemes (OFDM, QPSK, QAM, FSK, etc.), waveform/protocol parameters and packet structures.
Analyse and decode physical layer MIMO signal waveforms for LTE, 5G NR, Wi-Fi, and other wireless technologies.
Understand and analyse frequency-hopped TDMA, OFDMA and SC-FDMA packet structures, including frame layouts, signal transmission patterns, pilots and preambles, and control/data channels.
Develop algorithms for signal demodulation, synchronization, detection and decoding.
Develop and maintain evaluation pipelines for validating PHY layer protocols against real-world over-the-air captures.
Translate high-level signal processing algorithms into optimized, production-ready implementations for resource-constrained platforms.
Develop, optimise, and maintain DSP software embedded systems, ensuring high performance and low latency.
Implement and maintain CI/CD pipelines for DSP software development.
Provide technical guidance on DSP software architecture, ensuring scalability, maintainability, and performance.
Design and implement new software features for embedded Linux-based systems
Ensure software is designed for performance and reliability on resource constrained targets
Collaborate with multi-disciplinary teams to deliver on user and business requirements
Work with the broader engineering team to ensure reliable and robust end to end system operation
Write and maintain internal documentation for implemented features

Qualifications, Experience and Skills

Bachelor's (or higher) degree in Electrical Engineering, Computer Science, or a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience.
At least 5 years of experience in DSP software development, with a focus on embedded systems and resource-constrained platforms.
High proficiency with Python, including familiarity with Scipy, Numpy, Numba.
Firm understanding of Digital Signal Processing concepts, including filtering, FFTs, modulation/demodulation, and adaptive signal processing.
Knowledge of modern software development practices, DevSecOps, Test-Driven Development (TDD), version control (e.g., Git), automated testing, system monitoring and CI/CD pipelines.
Ability to work effectively in a multidisciplinary team, including collaborating with algorithms, hardware, and software engineers.
Ability to turn complex algorithms and mathematical models into high-performance software, operating on sensor data.
Working knowledge of modern architectural patterns and software design patterns.
Experience using modern C++ and/or Python to develop complex applications
Familiarity with developing under Linux (embedded Linux would be advantageous)
Experience with multi-process architectures (including IPC mechanisms)
Proficiency with multiple programming languages, especially C++, Python, and Go
Exposure to software architecture and design patterns
Experience with development tools including Git, Jira, Confluence, GitLab CI/CD, Docker, Poetry, Pyenv
The following would also be highly desirable:
Experience with concurrent computing and code optimisation
